text: It depends on what you want to do Christian. How does your deck normally play out? I know we’ve talked a bit about the differences between our Scarab God lists, but how does your function over all? What are some key cards and your wincons, aside from his triggered ability?

<@UGK9N4JJ2> basically currently it’s about getting as many zombies onto the field as possible and having a good zombie army. I have ways of using that to get card advantage, but I rarely use his eternalize ability and I usually win faster with things like paradox haze. I get a really cheap but developed zombie army that just nets me value and is a terrifying threat they can’t really deal with

Kethis updates for Eldraine:

- Saffi Eriksdotter -- cute protection but i'm not abusing it for combo, seems like something that does more could be in this slot
- Merciless Eviction -- part of my "add more boardwipes" to the deck, i will probably regret this since i dont have much artifact or enchantment removal in here
- Nissa, Vital Force -- not sure this does enough. I thought it would be cute to untap gaea's cardle, and in other times is a 5/5, but meh

+ The Great Henge -- duh (it's also legendary)
+ Rankle, Master of Prankles -- this guy is good in this deck, even self discard is not terrible, but making everyone sac a creature is good and i can get gas if i need... plus hes flying and haste
+ Syr Konrad, the Grim -- Good in this deck. Meaty 5/4. I guess he could fuel by milling. Could see him getting cut one day tbh if the ability isnt worth it

Chainer:
- Blood Artist -- im pretty much never doing an infinite loop to make blood artist help me win a game, though he does provide some incremental value
+ Witch's Cottage -- neat effect, can tutor it, can't stand to cut one of my foil snow-covered lands... more lands can never be bad!
i got a foil Ayara, First of Lochtwain but she didn't make it for the same reason that blood artist got cut
